description:
This is super important. I didn’t know what the program stood for so here’s what it is. 
The Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants, and Children (WIC) provides federal grants to states for supplemental foods, health care referrals, and nutrition education for low-income pregnant, breastfeeding, and non-breastfeeding postpartum women, and to infants and children up to age five who are found to be at nutritional risk. It’s only for those items so if you don’t need that all else being equal buy something else. #togetherapart
